vars <- c("Hinting", "Fauxpas", "IRIPT", "LN_sequencing", "TMTA_rev", "Coding", "Animals")

cor_res <- psych::corr.test(data1[, vars], use = "pairwise", method = "pearson")
cor_mat <- cor_res$r
p_mat   <- cor_res$p

# --- formateur 2 dÃ©cimales, zÃ©ros inclus
fmt2 <- function(x) formatC(x, digits = 2, format = "f")

stars <- function(p) {
  ifelse(p <= 0.001, "***",
         ifelse(p <= 0.01,  "**",
                ifelse(p <= 0.05, "*", "")))
}

# --- construit la matrice texte avec deux dÃ©cimales + Ã©toiles
cor_text <- matrix(
  paste0(fmt2(cor_mat), stars(p_mat)),
  nrow = nrow(cor_mat),
  dimnames = dimnames(cor_mat)
)

# diagonale vide
diag(cor_text) <- ""

# garder seulement le triangle supÃ©rieur
cor_tri <- cor_text
cor_tri[lower.tri(cor_tri)] <- ""

cor_df <- as.data.frame(cor_tri)
cor_df <- cbind(Variable = rownames(cor_df), cor_df)

variable_labels <- c(
  Hinting = "Hinting task",
  Fauxpas = "Faux Pas",
  IRIPT = "IRI PT",
  LN_sequencing = "Letter-Number",
  TMTA_rev = "TMT A",
  Coding = "Coding",
  Animals = "Fluency Animals"
)

colnames(cor_df)[-1] <- variable_labels[colnames(cor_df)[-1]]
cor_df$Variable <- variable_labels[cor_df$Variable]

# retirer la colonne auto-corrÃ©lation de Hinting si souhaitÃ©

S6. Test-retest reliability

test_retest_analysis <- function(data1, hinting_col, retest_col) {
  valid_rows <- !is.na(data1[[retest_col]])
  test_retest_data <- data1[valid_rows, c(hinting_col, retest_col)]
  
  cat("n =", nrow(test_retest_data), "\n")
  
  summary_stats <- describe(test_retest_data)
  print(summary_stats)
  
  icc_result <- ICC(test_retest_data)
  print(icc_result$results["Single_raters_absolute", "ICC"])
  
  icc_value <- icc_result$results["Single_raters_absolute", "ICC"]
  icc_lower <- icc_result$results["Single_raters_absolute", "lower bound"]
  icc_upper <- icc_result$results["Single_raters_absolute", "upper bound"]
  
  cat("ICC (Single raters, absolute agreement) =", round(icc_value, 3), 
      "IC95% [", round(icc_lower, 3), ";", round(icc_upper, 3), "]\n")
}

test_retest_analysis(data1, "Hinting", "Hinting_Retest")

S7. Pratice effect

analyze_practice_effect <- function(score1, score2, label) {
  
  valid_rows <- complete.cases(score1, score2)
  s1 <- score1[valid_rows]
  s2 <- score2[valid_rows]
  
  cat("\n---", label, "---\n")
  cat("N =", length(s1), "\n")
  
  # Moyenne et Ã©cart-type des diffÃ©rences
  mean_diff <- mean(s1 - s2)
  sd_diff <- sd(s1 - s2)
  cat("Mean difference =", round(mean_diff, 2), 
      "(SD =", round(sd_diff, 2), ")\n")
  
  # Test t
  ttest <- t.test(s1, s2, paired = TRUE)
  print(ttest)
  
  # Taille d'effet
  dz <- cohens_d(s1, s2, paired = TRUE)
  cat("Cohen's dz :", round(dz$Cohens_d, 3), 
      "| IC95% [", round(dz$CI_low, 3), ";", round(dz$CI_high, 3), "]\n")
}
analyze_practice_effect( data1$Hinting_Retest, data1$Hinting, "Hinting")
